</p>

<hr>

<h2>рџ“Њ Project Overview</h2>

<p>
This project uses <b>Deep Learning and Transfer Learning</b> to detect speed breakers from road images.
The model is trained using <b>MobileNetV2</b>, a lightweight convolutional neural network pretrained on ImageNet.
</p>

<p>
The system also includes a <b>Streamlit web application</b> where users can upload a road image and the model will predict whether a speed breaker is present.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>рџ“Њ Features</h2>

<ul>
<li>Deep Learning based road image classification</li>
<li>Transfer Learning using MobileNetV2</li>
<li>Image preprocessing pipeline</li>
<li>Streamlit web application for real-time predictions</li>
<li>Clean machine learning project structure</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>рџ§  Model Architecture</h2>

<pre>
Road Image
   в†“
Image Preprocessing
   в†“
MobileNetV2 Feature Extractor
   в†“
Global Average Pooling
   в†“
Dense Layer
   в†“
Binary Classification
   в†“
Prediction (Speed Breaker / Normal Road)
</pre>

